reviewText: A very enjoyable concert film. All the great songs are performed. It's a fun, energetic concert.  Also has a pretty decent 5.1 audio mix. Bonus features includes a documentary of the band and photo stills.

reviewText: I LOVE THIS!!  The live show is Awesome--so Great to see the Original Fab 5 back together and performing like the years hadn't passed by. There is Energy and Nostalgia--New Songs mixed in with  songs from throughout their 20+ years. There is Great behind the scenes interviews and a Wonderful Bonus feature where they each talk a bit about 2 different song--total of 10 songs--and what they mean, or how they came to be, or some memories of  writing--INTERESTING!!!
summary: IF YOU'RE A FAN YOU HAVE TO GET THIS!!!

reviewText: This concert is really good.  I'm not a big Duran Duran fan, but I have to say that they put on an excellent show and they sound exactly like their albums.DVD rating:Content: 10 out of 10.  Every major song was on the playlist, my favorite "Rio" being the grand finale; about 1 hour 30 minutes and 20 songs.  There is even a 20 minute documentary on their history.Sound: 10 out of 10.  No flaws - 4 choices of audio, Dolby Digital 5.1, SBS 5.1, Pro Logic, DTS 5.1 (the best of course).  It has excellent ambiance, and detailed lows and highs.Picture: 6.5 out of 10.  Despite being advertised as filmed in HD, the transfer had many artifacts at long range.  Not all cameras were HD and that was apparent in the transfer.  The colors were vibrant and the picture wasn't bad.  It is wide-screen aspect.I plugged in the sub, but forgot to turn it on, and it still had excellent bass.  I later tried it with the sub, and thought that I would either have to turn the sub down or not use it at all.  I played it between -20 and -18 dbs, and after the concert was over, my ears kinda hurt.  It was like actually being at a concert.

reviewText: This might be the last time we see the original five members perform together as Andy Taylor has left for the second time.It's pure Duran Duran from start to finish belting out most of their best loved hits. Minor quibble - no New Moon On Monday or My Own Way.Still, it's a great concert video and even if you weren't there, you will be dancing in front of the TV. It's THAT infectious. Takes me back to those teen parties when Duran Duran were the hottest band in the world. Now where's my padded jacket?
summary: Last Chance To See Original Line Up!
